message.content:
We can compute each metric step by step.

1. Return on Equity (ROE):
• ROE is calculated as Net Profit divided by the average owner's equity over the period.
• Beginning Owner's Equity = 13,000,000.00  
• Ending Owner's Equity = 14,095,371.35  
• Average Owner's Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 14,095,371.35) / 2 = 13,547,685.68  
• Net Profit from the income statement = 1,095,371.35  
• ROE = 1,095,371.35 / 13,547,685.68 ≈ 0.0809 or 8.09%

2. Debt to Asset Ratio:
• Total Liabilities can be derived from the balance sheet since:  
  Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity − Total Owner's Equity  
• Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity (End) = 14,823,650.85  
• Total Owner's Equity (End) = 14,095,371.35  
• Therefore, Total Liabilities = 14,823,650.85 − 14,095,371.35 = 728,279.50  
• Total Assets (End) = 14,823,650.85  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 728,279.50 / 14,823,650.85 ≈ 0.0492 (approximately 0.05 when rounded)

3. Gross Profit Margin:
• Gross Profit Margin is computed as Gross Profit divided by Total Revenue.
• Gross Profit (from income statement) = 2,545,589.48  
• Total Revenue = 5,565,589.48  
• Gross Profit Margin = (2,545,589.48 / 5,565,589.48) ≈ 0.4578 or 45.78%

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "8.09%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.05",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.78%"
  }
}
